	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_000457_0001"/><!--pb/@n='01'-->
<lb/><p rend="left"><hi rend="underline">To <persName>Janet Livingston</persName></hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">My Dear Sister </p>
<lb/><p>I send you these lines which 
<lb/>I received as a reliquaire from my friend <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Banff</persName>. 
<lb/>Accept them as a token of my unabated affection, and 
<lb/>sincere wish that the Christian's exalted hope may 
<lb/>be your portion through life; and though we may not 
<lb/>meet again in Time, that you and all my beloved 
<lb/>relatives and friends, may meet where separation 
<lb/>and sorrow are unknown, to sing the praises of 
<lb/>our dear Redeeemer, who loved &amp; gave himself for us. </p>
<lb/><p rend="center">Your Affectionate Brother </p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><hi rend="underline"><persName>David Livingston</persName></hi></p>
<lb/><p rend="left"><placeName>Ongar,</placeName><placeName>Essex,</placeName> Oct<hi rend="sup">r</hi> 3 <hi rend="sup">d</hi>/58 </p>
			
</div>
